So to respond a bit.
The world I'm setting the dwarf sheep in, isn't the standard fantasy fair. It's going to be more science fantasy than anything.
The lore I have worked out is, that these are literal dwarves, but somewhere in their past they pissed off, legend says, some powerful being who cursed them with their sheepish forms.
It actually mellowed them out to a degree and they left the mountains for the plains and grasslands evnetually adopting a Southern type dialect, and their culture does chance to reflect this.
They still dig in the earth, only now it's for planting crops. They are still master smiths but for hoes, spades, plows and the like. Runic magic is still known to them and widely practiced.
I've got some other ideas that incorporate both some aspects of traditional dwarves and the fact that they are now sheep people.
